Notebook[{
Cell["OrthogonalCoordinates", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"4b927b24-0a63-4ed8-b9ae-45e93c051910"],

Cell["\<\
OrthogonalCoordinates[graph, axes, v] returns the n-tuple of layer indices, \
one per axis, of v's shortest-path projection onto each axis (non-negative \
integers from each axis's path start). Each axis is a vertex list (line) or a \
directed acyclic graph (DAG). OrthogonalCoordinates[graph, axes] returns the \
Association of n-tuples for every vertex. OrthogonalCoordinates[graph, c, v] \
auto-discovers orthogonal axes through center vertex c via FindOrthogonalAxes \
and returns the Z-valued signed displacement of v from c. \
OrthogonalCoordinates[graph, c] returns the Association of all signed \
coordinates with c at the origin. OrthogonalCoordinates[graph, \
InfraPoint[{v1, ..., vk}], v] takes axes that contain at least one of the \
listed vertices as an interior point; signing uses the first such vertex per \
axis. Options: \"Origin\" -> vertex (signs coordinates relative to that \
origin when explicit axes are given); \"Aggregation\" -> \"First\" | \"Last\" \
| \"Min\" | \"Max\" | \"Mean\" | \"Median\" -- how to reduce tied layer \
indices when several axis vertices are equidistant from v.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"60d95ee1-1c57-4f44-90e1-4a5a9818eaa9"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"94020226-0358-4c3f-a381-dfad5f84bde5"],

Cell["Load the paclet before running the examples on this page.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"ff73ef7e-a8e9-4f7b-9026-fd01a7642dc1"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"167c9827-2deb-4c6d-b048-11e0daa42189"],

Cell["Usage", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"21570753-41f8-443e-907e-7179baf5ef1c"],

Cell["\<\
Cartesian coordinates on a 4 x 4 grid via the bottom row and left column as \
axes.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"52a6e258-94a8-4893-b085-39c455178b8f"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{4, 4}], xAxis = {1, 2, 3, 4}, yAxis = {1, 5, 9, 13}}, \
OrthogonalCoordinates[g, {xAxis, yAxis}, 11]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a4c5ae41-5756-4761-9cf6-d185cee6851b"],

Cell["Bulk form: the entire grid coordinatized.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"80c29bdc-1136-41c8-89e6-1a126c7646dc"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{4, 4}], xAxis = {1, 2, 3, 4}, yAxis = {1, 5, 9, 13}}, \
OrthogonalCoordinates[g, {xAxis, yAxis}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"c686665e-aa3f-41b7-93f6-5e98b07247e0"],

Cell["\<\
Center-based form: signed Z-valued displacements with the path midpoint at \
the origin.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"a0e0bb92-437f-4986-9869-a756bd575756"],

Cell["OrthogonalCoordinates[PathGraph[Range[5]], 3]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"593bed34-0890-42a8-8733-a7efbba4411e"],

Cell["Examples", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d8b278ea-13b9-40c4-8c05-7e9dfd8acfda"],

Cell["\<\
Tied projection on the 4-cycle: vertex 4 has graph distance 1 to both 1 and 3 \
on the axis {1, 2, 3} -- ties at positions 1 and 3 (0-indexed: 0 and 2). \
Different aggregations give different coordinates.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"c821a0e0-3de3-4d31-888b-83b11233d138"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = CycleGraph[4], axis = {{1, 2, 3}}}, Table[mode -> \
OrthogonalCoordinates[g, axis, 4, \"Aggregation\" -> mode], {mode, \
{\"First\", \"Last\", \"Min\", \"Max\", \"Mean\", \"Median\"}}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"9a471be9-c737-4514-9eb7-edca91abad5b"],

Cell["\<\
Explicit origin: signed displacement of vertex 11 from vertex 6 on the 4 x 4 \
grid.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"b114fd21-0d51-4185-acaa-65fdc7d6d83b"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{4, 4}], xAxis = {1, 2, 3, 4}, yAxis = {1, 5, 9, 13}}, \
OrthogonalCoordinates[g, {xAxis, yAxis}, 11, \"Origin\" -> 6]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"3fcad53c-859a-4dec-918f-f924bdd9d99a"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPoint center: a multi-vertex anchor in which each axis must pass through \
at least one of the listed vertices.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"4e8334ed-444c-4105-a22c-a0ec919a7f92"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = GridGraph[{5, 5}], anchors = {7, 19}}, OrthogonalCoordinates[g, \
InfraPoint[anchors]]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d054affd-ec0d-4b64-a6b5-86de3da36a9d"],

Cell["\<\
DAG axis: a directed acyclic graph instead of a vertex list as axis. Layers \
are sliced by shortest-path distance from sources.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"bb1ab585-d826-4546-8e6e-ed156cd6d508"],

Cell["\<\
With[{g = PathGraph[Range[5]], dag = Graph[{DirectedEdge[1, 2], \
DirectedEdge[2, 3]}]}, OrthogonalCoordinates[g, {dag}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"80ddaf34-c4ed-4cff-a86b-eaa0027e0a2e"],

Cell["See also", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a65ce2e7-c168-4dbb-a85e-150f5d111d81"],

Cell["FindOrthogonalAxes", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1536f595-876d-4b69-8d6f-b48b2270130e"],

Cell["RadarCoordinates", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5bf57c48-c3e7-4fb2-a6f9-337e42d575b8"],

Cell["FindRadarBasis", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"aaa423f2-4600-49d3-a99c-ad91979240a7"],

Cell["InfraPoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0e11aca9-fca4-4b6b-9b9a-375ce73f8c2d"],

Cell["CoordinatizationGuide", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4d22e66e-80cd-4bcb-820e-a037e4ad644b"]
},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
